In small bowl, combine marinade, sauce, broth and cornstarch. Set aside. Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. Brown chicken breast tenders for 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden brown. Remove chicken from skillet; cover to keep warm. Add onion, broccoli and carrot to skillet; cook and stir 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Return chicken to skillet. Stir cornstarch mixture until smooth. Add to skillet; cook and stir until sauce is bubbly and thickened. Serve over chow mien noodles and sprinkled chopped cashews.